  27 def init(complete_options=False, match_incomplete=None):
  28     """Initialize the enhanced click completion
  29 
  30     Parameters
  31     ----------
  32     complete_options : bool
  33         always complete the options, even when the user hasn't typed a first dash (Default value = False)
  34     match_incomplete : func
  35         a function with two parameters choice and incomplete. Must return True
  36         if incomplete is a correct match for choice, False otherwise.
  37     """
  38     global _initialized
  39     if not _initialized:
  40         _patch()
  41         completion_configuration.complete_options = complete_options
  42         if match_incomplete is not None:
  43             completion_configuration.match_incomplete = match_incomplete
  44         _initialized = True
  45 
  46 
  47 class DocumentedChoice(ParamType):
  48     """The choice type allows a value to be checked against a fixed set of
  49     supported values.  All of these values have to be strings. Each value may
  50     be associated to a help message that will be display in the error message
  51     and during the completion.
  52 
  53     Parameters
  54     ----------
  55     choices : dict or Enum
  56         A dictionary with the possible choice as key, and the corresponding help string as value
  57     """
  58     name = 'choice'
  59 
  60     def __init__(self, choices):
  61         if isinstance(choices, Enum):
  62             self.choices = dict((choice.name, choice.value) for choice in choices)
  63         else:
  64             self.choices = dict(choices)
  65 
  66     def get_metavar(self, param):
  67         return '[%s]' % '|'.join(self.choices.keys())
  68 
  69     def get_missing_message(self, param):
  70         formated_choices = ['{:<12} {}'.format(k, self.choices[k] or '') for k in sorted(self.choices.keys())]
  71         return 'Choose from\n  ' + '\n  '.join(formated_choices)
  72 
  73     def convert(self, value, param, ctx):
  74         # Exact match
  75         if value in self.choices:
  76             return value
  77 
  78         # Match through normalization
  79         if ctx is not None and \
  80            ctx.token_normalize_func is not None:
  81             value = ctx.token_normalize_func(value)
  82             for choice in self.choices:
  83                 if ctx.token_normalize_func(choice) == value:
  84                     return choice
  85 
  86         self.fail('invalid choice: %s. %s' %
  87                   (value, self.get_missing_message(param)), param, ctx)
  88 
  89     def __repr__(self):
  90         return 'DocumentedChoice(%r)' % list(self.choices.keys())
  91 
  92     def complete(self, ctx, incomplete):
  93         match = completion_configuration.match_incomplete
  94         return [(c, v) for c, v in six.iteritems(self.choices) if match(c, incomplete)]
